Census Data is provided by (https://www.socialexplorer.com/data/ACS2019_5yr/metadata/?ds=ACS19_5yr)

Download Census Data for 2015-2019

pr_population19 <- get_acs(geography = "tract", 
     variables = c("total_pop19" = "B01003_001", #Total Population
                   "median_hh19" = "B19013_001", #Median Household Income in the Past 12 Months
                   "total_ins19" = "B27001_001" #Total Health Insurance Coverage 
                   ), 
     year = 2019,
     survey = "acs5",
     state = c(72),
     geometry = TRUE, # download the shapefile with the data
     output = "wide") # need this
## Getting data from the 2015-2019 5-year ACS

pr_population19$inspct <- pr_population19$total_ins19E / pr_population19$total_ins19E

filter_na = pr_population19 %>% filter(!is.na(pr_population19$median_hh19E))

filter_na <- bi_class(filter_na, x= total_ins19E, y= median_hh19E, style = "quantile", dim = 3)
hghst_con = filter_na %>% filter(median_hh19E == 101125)
